South Africa’s ANC Favors Chile’s Mining Policy, City Press Says

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-12-11T09:35:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/south-africa-s-anc-favors-chile-s-mining-policy-city-press-says.html
South Africa ’s ruling  African
National Congress  is leaning toward the partial nationalization
of the  mining industry , following an approach adopted by  Chile ,
 City Press  reported, citing unidentified people.  The ANC last year commissioned three economists to study
nationalizing the mining industry. The panel’s findings will be
discussed by the party’s national executive committee on Jan.
30, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing Enoch Godongwana, head of an ANC task force overseeing the study.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in  Cape Town  at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 